  "CAN-027": "# CAN-027: Saddle Lake\n**Date:** 1979\n**Location:**  (53.9, -111.6)\n**Classification:** CE1\n\n## Case Summary\n\nIn 1979, one or more witnesses reported an unidentified aerial phenomenon near Saddle Lake, AB. The object was described as Triangle. Classification: CE1 (Hynek). Witness: First Nations Community. Evidence: Silent, low-level flight. Source: Community Logs.\n\n## Witnesses\n\n**Count:** 5\n**Description:** First Nations Community\n**Credibility:** Low\n\n## Physical Evidence\n\n- Silent, low-level flight\n\n## Pattern Tags\n\n`mass-sighting`",
  "CAN-028": "# CAN-028: Portage la Prairie\n**Date:** 1979\n**Location:**  (49.9724, -98.2892)\n**Classification:** DD\n\n## Case Summary\n\nIn 1979, military personnel at CFB Portage la Prairie, Manitoba reported a large metallic cigar-shaped object hovering over the base runway for over 20 minutes. Base searchlights were reportedly directed at the object, but the light appeared to bend or pass around it without illuminating it clearly. The object was tracked on base radar. It eventually departed at extreme velocity, disappearing from radar in seconds. The incident was documented in MUFON files and the Winnipeg Sun archives.\n\n## Witnesses\n\n**Count:** 3\n**Description:** Military personnel at CFB Portage la Prairie. Large metallic cigar-shaped object hovered over runway for 20+ minutes. Searchlights seemed to bend around it. Object departed at extreme velocity.\n**Credibility:** High\n\n## Physical Evidence\n\n- Base radar operator statements\n- Sketches of metallic cylindrical object\n\n## Official Reports\n\n- MUFON — Archived under Manitoba Military Files 1979\n\n## Media\n\n- https://winnipegsun.com/archives/1979/11/ufo-over-portage\n- https://www.ufoofthewestcanada.ca/1979-portage-la-prairies\n\n## Pattern Tags\n\n`military-involvement` `nocturnal-light` `physical-evidence` `radar-visual`",
  "CAN-029": "# CAN-029: Nahanni Valley\n**Date:** 1980\n**Location:**  (61.2, -124.0)\n**Classification:** NL\n\n## Case Summary\n\nIn 1980, one or more witnesses reported an unidentified aerial phenomenon near Nahanni Valley, NT. The object was described as Glowing Orbs. Witness: Adventurers. Evidence: Orbs following hikers. Source: \"Headless Valley\" Lore.\n\n## Witnesses\n\n**Count:** 2\n**Description:** Adventurers\n**Credibility:** Low\n\n## Physical Evidence\n\n- Orbs following hikers\n\n## Pattern Tags\n\n`nocturnal-light`",
  "CAN-030": "# CAN-030: L'Ancienne-Lorette\n**Date:** 1987\n**Location:**  (46.8, -71.4)\n**Classification:** CE1\n\n## Case Summary\n\nIn 1987, two Quebec provincial police (Sureté du Quebec) officers on highway patrol near L'Ancienne-Lorette, Quebec witnessed a hovering disc-shaped object with rotating multicolored lights. The object emitted a low-frequency hum before accelerating silently upward and disappearing into the cloud layer. Both officers signed a joint affidavit and filed an official SQ incident report. Law enforcement witnesses give this case high credibility.\n\n## Witnesses\n\n**Count:** 2\n**Description:** Quebec provincial police (SQ) officers on highway patrol witnessed a hovering, disc-shaped object with rotating multicolored lights. Object emitted low-frequency hum before accelerating silently into cloud layer.\n**Credibility:** High\n\n**Occupation:** Law Enforcement — SQ Officers\n\n## Physical Evidence\n\n- Official SQ incident report logs\n- Joint affidavit signed by two officers\n\n## Official Reports\n\n- SQ — Official SQ incident report logs\n\n## Media\n\n- https://www.lesoleil.com/archives/1987/03/30/ovni-policiers\n\n## Pattern Tags\n\n`close-encounter` `daylight-disc` `multiple-craft` `police-involved`",
